Impressed by these positive recommendations we decided to go to Emperor's Choice and were totally dissapointed. We both are passionate cooks, eaters and lovers of chinese food. The selection of seafood we ordered (shrimps, scallops)was not authentic at all and had neither chinese aroma, spices and vegetables, nor just good taste. There were several ingredients just missing like fresh ginger, several herbes, garlic, onion, harmonic pepperness and spiciness. Although the scallops and shrimps were of great quality, the cook had no idea how to prepare those ingredients tasty. What we got were oversalted scallops in a fabric finished product sauce, shrimps just in a tomato-like sauce (is this chinese?) and diep fried butterfly-shrimps which consisted only of breeding. We will never eat there again and never recommend this restaurant to someone else.
